    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hi @daveiglu \r\n\r\nIndeed from the InstantSearch perspective there is only the `render` event. Underneath, however there are other events managed by the [JS Helper](https://community.algolia.com/algoliasearch-helper-js/). For example, there is [an event where new results](https://community.algolia.com/algoliasearch-helper-js/reference.html#AlgoliaSearchHelper#event:result) are received:\r\n\r\n```js\r\n// after search.start() has been called\r\nsearch.helper.on('result', (results, state) => {\r\n  // results contains the actual results\r\n  // state contains the state used to generate those results\r\n});\r\n```",
